Below is an example of a simple todo application's API contract with three endpoints:

Auth
POST /api/auth/recipient/register
Registers a new recipient account with wallet address (pending admin approval).
Request:
Body: { full_name, recipient_email, password, wallet_address }
All fields required.
Response:
Success: { recipient_id, full_name, recipient_email, wallet_address, is_eligible } 201
Error, Validation: { message } 400 — invalid wallet address format, missing field
Error, Conflict: { message } 409 — email or wallet address already exists
POST /api/auth/recipient/login
Authenticates a recipient and returns a session token.
Request:
Body: { recipient_email, password }
Response:
Success: { token, recipient_id, full_name } 200
Error, Invalid Credentials: { message } 401
POST /api/auth/admin/login
Authenticates an administrator and returns a session token.
Request:
Body: { administrator_name, password }
Response:
Success: { token, administrator_id, administrator_name } 200
Error, Invalid Credentials: { message } 401

Recipients
GET /api/recipients
Returns all recipients. Admin only.
Request:
Body: None
Optional ?is_eligible=true or ?is_eligible=false query string to filter by eligibility status
Response:
Success: [{ recipient_id, full_name, recipient_email, wallet_address, is_eligible, enrolled_at }, {...}, …] 200
Error, Not Authenticated: { message } 401
Error, Unauthorized: { message } 403
GET /api/recipients/:id
Returns a single recipient's profile, including disbursement history summary. A recipient may only fetch their own record; an admin may fetch any.
Request:
Body: None
Response:
Success: { recipient_id, full_name, recipient_email, wallet_address, is_eligible, enrolled_at, next_disbursement_date } 200
Error, Not Authenticated: { message } 401
Error, Unauthorized: { message } 403
Error, Not Found: { message } 404
POST /api/recipients
Enrolls a new recipient (admin-approved path — distinct from self-registration). Admin only.
Request:
Body: { full_name, recipient_email, wallet_address }
All fields required. is_eligible defaults to true and is not settable on creation.
Response:
Success: { recipient_id, full_name, recipient_email, wallet_address, is_eligible } 201
Error, Not Authenticated: { message } 401
Error, Unauthorized: { message } 403
Error, Validation: { message } 400
PATCH /api/recipients/:id/revoke
Revokes a recipient's eligibility, removing them from future disbursement cycles. Admin only.
Request:
Body: None
Response:
Success: { recipient_id, is_eligible: false, revoked_at } 200
Error, Not Authenticated: { message } 401
Error, Unauthorized: { message } 403
Error, Not Found: { message } 404
PATCH /api/recipients/:id/reinstate
Restores a previously revoked recipient's eligibility. Admin only.
Request:
Body: None
Response:
Success: { recipient_id, is_eligible: true, revoked_at: null } 200
Error, Not Authenticated: { message } 401
Error, Unauthorized: { message } 403
Error, Not Found: { message } 404

Disbursement Cycles
GET /api/cycles
Returns all disbursement cycles. Admin only.
Request:
Body: None
Optional ?status=pending, ?status=processing, ?status=completed, or ?status=failed query string to filter by cycle status
Response:
Success: [{ cycle_id, scheduled_date, triggered_at, amount_per_recipient, total_recipients, status }, {...}, …] 200
Error, Not Authenticated: { message } 401
Error, Unauthorized: { message } 403
GET /api/cycles/:id
Returns a single cycle's details, including the full on-chain disbursement log for that cycle. Admin only.
Request:
Body: None
Response:
Success: { cycle_id, scheduled_date, triggered_at, amount_per_recipient, total_recipients, status, disbursements: [{ disbursement_id, recipient_id, amount, tx_hash, status, disbursed_at }, {...}] } 200
Error, Not Authenticated: { message } 401
Error, Unauthorized: { message } 403
Error, Not Found: { message } 404
POST /api/cycles
Schedules a new disbursement cycle (does not execute it yet). Admin only.
Request:
Body: { scheduled_date, amount_per_recipient }
Both fields required.
Response:
Success: { cycle_id, scheduled_date, amount_per_recipient, total_recipients, status: 'pending' } 201
Error, Not Authenticated: { message } 401
Error, Unauthorized: { message } 403
Error, Validation: { message } 400
POST /api/cycles/:id/trigger
Triggers the smart contract to execute USDC transfers to all eligible recipients in this cycle as a batch. Admin only.
Request:
Body: None
Response:
Success: { cycle_id, status: 'processing', triggered_at } 202 — processing is async; poll GET /api/cycles/:id for completion
Error, Not Authenticated: { message } 401
Error, Unauthorized: { message } 403
Error, Not Found: { message } 404
Error, Insufficient Funds: { message } 409 — funding pool balance too low to cover cycle
Error, Already Triggered: { message } 409 — cycle is not in 'pending' status

Disbursements
GET /api/recipients/:id/disbursements
Returns a recipient's full disbursement history. A recipient may only fetch their own; an admin may fetch any.
Request:
Body: None
Optional ?limit=20&offset=0 for pagination (defaults: limit=20, offset=0)
Response:
Success: [{ disbursement_id, cycle_id, amount, tx_hash, status, disbursed_at }, {...}, …] 200
Error, Not Authenticated: { message } 401
Error, Unauthorized: { message } 403
Error, Not Found: { message } 404
GET /api/disbursements/:id
Returns a single disbursement record, including its transaction hash for on-chain verification.
Request:
Body: None
Response:
Success: { disbursement_id, cycle_id, recipient_id, amount, tx_hash, status, disbursed_at } 200
Error, Not Authenticated: { message } 401
Error, Unauthorized: { message } 403
Error, Not Found: { message } 404

Funding Pool
GET /api/funding-pool
Returns the current cached funding pool balance. Admin only.
Request:
Body: None
Response:
Success: { pool_id, balance, last_synced_at } 200
Error, Not Authenticated: { message } 401
Error, Unauthorized: { message } 403
POST /api/funding-pool/sync
Re-syncs the cached balance against the on-chain USDC balance. Admin only.
Request:
Body: None
Response:
Success: { pool_id, balance, last_synced_at } 200
Error, Not Authenticated: { message } 401
Error, Unauthorized: { message } 403
Error, Chain Unreachable: { message } 502

Audit Log
GET /api/audit-log
Returns the full audit trail of administrator actions. Admin only.
Request:
Body: None
Optional ?action_type=trigger_disbursement query string to filter by action type
Optional ?limit=50&offset=0 for pagination (defaults: limit=50, offset=0)
Response:
Success: [{ log_id, administrator_id, action_type, target_recipient_id, details, created_at }, {...}, …] 200
Error, Not Authenticated: { message } 401
Error, Unauthorized: { message } 403

A couple of design notes worth flagging:
Async triggering: POST /api/cycles/:id/trigger returns 202 Accepted rather than 200, since a batch on-chain transaction can't complete instantly — the client should poll GET /api/cycles/:id for status.
Self-registration vs. admin enrollment: I split these into two endpoints (/api/auth/recipient/register and POST /api/recipients) since your user stories describe both a recipient registering themselves and an admin adding/approving wallets — you may want to collapse these into one flow with a pending eligibility state if your actual UX only has one path in.
